  "detailed_description": "Duline is a pure and simple logic game, expressing unexpected complexity through its level design.<br><br>31 unique levels. The game is quite challenging so be prepared.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1932430/extras/6016978f067f570458f991f6d9e68c26.poster.avif?t=1651543219\" width=510 height=508 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1932430/extras/6016978f067f570458f991f6d9e68c26.webm?t=1651543219\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1932430/extras/6016978f067f570458f991f6d9e68c26.mp4?t=1651543219\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Rules:</h2><br>You can place blue or orange blocks anywhere except white tiles.<br><br>The goal is to cover all the green tiles on the board with the least 'chains' used.<br><br>A chain is when blocks of the same colour touch in the main cardinal directions.<br>Chains over 12 in length are invalid!",
  "about_the_game": "Duline is a pure and simple logic game, expressing unexpected complexity through its level design.<br><br>31 unique levels. The game is quite challenging so be prepared.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1932430/extras/6016978f067f570458f991f6d9e68c26.poster.avif?t=1651543219\" width=510 height=508 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1932430/extras/6016978f067f570458f991f6d9e68c26.webm?t=1651543219\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1932430/extras/6016978f067f570458f991f6d9e68c26.mp4?t=1651543219\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Rules:</h2><br>You can place blue or orange blocks anywhere except white tiles.<br><br>The goal is to cover all the green tiles on the board with the least 'chains' used.<br><br>A chain is when blocks of the same colour touch in the main cardinal directions.<br>Chains over 12 in length are invalid!",
